    "An example of this structure is provided in Table 6 in the Appendix A.",
    "Finally, we derive the posterior empirical distribution of national incidence by summing the counts across areas for each sample s, meaning we do a columnwise sum of Table 6 in the Appendix A, resulting in S samples of national incidence for each year.",
    "Table 3 presents the observed national incidence counts alongside the estimated mean national incidence counts and 95% credible intervals for each model during the validation period from 2001 to 2013.",
